Java 11 Daily Coding Useful Features:

- var in lambda parameters – Shorter syntax, useful with annotations.

- New String methods: isBlank(), strip(), stripLeading(), stripTrailing(), lines(), repeat(int)

- Files methods:
Files.readString(Path)
Files.writeString(Path, String)

- List.copyOf(), Set.copyOf(), Map.copyOf() – Immutable copies of collections.

- Optional.isEmpty() – Clearer alternative to !isPresent().

- Run .java without javac – Single-file execution from CLI.

Java 11 Non-Daily / Skip for Most Projects:

- HTTP Client API (standardized after being incubating in Java 9 & 10) – useful only if you directly make HTTP requests without libraries like OkHttp.
- Flight Recorder & Mission Control – monitoring, mostly for production profiling.
- New Pattern and Matcher methods – rare unless you do heavy regex work.
- Deprecation/removal of old Java EE modules (CORBA, JAXB, etc.).
- Epsilon GC – niche performance tuning.
- Nest-based access control – JVM-level security feature.
- Local-variable syntax for lambda parameters (already counted above in useful list).